            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25135",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This bug is not fixed...\n\nFix Version\/s  \t Next Mini Release (1.5.3) [ 10161 ]\nFix Version\/s  \t 1.6.1 [ 10201 ]\n\n\nBut still not working in 1.6.2!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-14T08:33:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-14T08:33:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27082",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Need some info:\n\nWhat version of PHP?\nWhat version of MSSQL?\nWhich driver are you using?  Presumably pdo_mssql? or are you using the odbc driver?\n\nThanks,\nRalph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-05T09:20:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-05T09:20:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27092",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello,\n\nI'm using PHP 5.2.6. MSSQL Server 2005. Using pdo_mssql.\nYou can get more information of other people having the same problem in the link above ( http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=38805 ). This is an old bug, why is it not fixed?\n\nThis seems to be a bug in php itself, not in Zend_Db (I think, you have to check that).... But we cannot use Zend_Db with this bug. Perhaps you have better connections to php-developers to fix this soon!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-05T16:06:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-05T16:06:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27119",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I believe this is an issue with the PDO MSSQL driver. It was one of the reasons I actually wrote a Zend_Db adapter to use the Microsoft SQL Server Driver for PHP for our sites that use ZF and SQL Server.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-08T06:48:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-08T06:48:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27182",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Steph Fox is currently looking to create a fix for pdo_mssql. We had a long discussion about this. Wez Furlong also helpt to get things very clear.\n\nAs I cannot fix pdo_mssql I could do something else: add support for odbc in Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Mssql.\n\nI will provide two patches that will offer this support. Note that is not a fix for the php bug. It is an improvement (I hope) that will let you use a workaround by going through pdo_odbc instead of pdo_mssql.\n\nIn order for this workaround to work, you will have to enable php_pdo_odbc.dll in your php.ini if you are working on Windows.\n\nIn addition, you will have to add extra options when you instantiate your Zend_Db_Adapter:\n\n{code}\n$db = Zend_Db::factory('Pdo_Mssql', array(\n                                     'pdoType' => 'odbc',\/\/extra\n                                     'DRIVER'   => '{SQL Server}',\/\/extra\n                                     'host'   => $server,\/\/required = $_SERVER['COMPUTERNAME']\n                                     'username' => '*************',\n                                     'password' => '*************',\n                                     'dbname'    => '*************',\n                                 )); \n{code}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T03:12:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T03:12:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27183",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patches added for odbc support so that you can use this workaround.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T03:16:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T03:16:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27184",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assign to component owner for evalutation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T03:17:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T03:17:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27186",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\nWith the new odbc-2 patch you do not need to specify the extra DRIVER option, only the pdoType option:\n\n{code}\n$db = Zend_Db::factory('Pdo_Mssql', array(\n                                     'pdoType' => 'odbc',\n                                     'host'   => $server,\n                                     'username' => $user,\n                                     'password' => $pass,\n                                     'dbname'    => $dbname,\n                                 ));\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T05:02:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T05:02:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27187",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I changed it from Bug to Patch, because there now is a patch that you can use. Besides, this is not a bug in ZF, it is a bug in pdo_mssql. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T05:09:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T05:09:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34136",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you please check 5.2.10, the php.net site claims this limitation does not exist in that version:\n\nhttp:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=38805\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-01T07:51:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-01T07:51:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34152",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tested on Windows Vista BU against 5.2.10 (which was a pain to get working...), confirmed that the problem still exists\n{code}\n<?php\n\/\/phpinfo();\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Loader\/AutoLoader.php';\n$loader = Zend_Loader_AutoLoader::getInstance();\n\n$db = Zend_Db::factory('Pdo_Mssql', array(\n                                     'pdoType' => 'mssql',\n                                     'host'   => 'HIGHLANDER',\n                                     'username' => '*',\n                                     'password' => '*',\n                                     'dbname'    => '*',\n                                 ));\n\n$result = $db->query('SELECT top 1 inhoudtekst1 as tekst FROM O_ProductenInhoud WHERE DATALENGTH(inhoudtekst1) > 4096');\n\nforeach($result as $row) {\n    var_dump($row['tekst']);\n}\n\nexit();\n{code}\n\nThe result is a truncated text of exactly 4096 chars, as var_dump conveniently reports.\nI must add that I had to download the ntwdblib.dll and replace the one that is shipped with php, because that one does not work at all (part of the pain of getting this installed). I also had to put it in system32.\n\nI also added these settings in php.ini:\n; Valid range 0 - 2147483647.  Default = 4096.\nmssql.textlimit = 2147483647\n\n; Valid range 0 - 2147483647.  Default = 4096.\nmssql.textsize = 2147483647",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-01T15:46:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-01T15:46:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37110",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Which patch should I be looking at?\r\n\r\nAlso, in very succinct terms, what exactly is the proposed solution?  I've tried creating an ODBC driver for Zend_Db but it does not pass QA (there are alot of feature missing, the standard unit tests fail, see ZF-905).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-21T12:54:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-21T12:54:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37124",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
